    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I noticed a minor API change when moving from earlier release to 1.3.x. Previously pushing data to already ended call stream got silently ignored, but now it's causing segfault. That could be the thing you are experiencing.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst inputStream = ....;\r\nconst call = grpc.clientStreaming((err, res) => {\r\n  // If this is called before the input stream has ended (e.g. in case of error)\r\n  // you have to unpipe or make sure some otherway that data is no more\r\n  // pushed to call.\r\n  inputStream.unpipe(call);\r\n});\r\ninputStream.pipe(call);\r\n```"
  },
